channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Over 2,000 people arrested at protests disrupting colleges across the US
item.description: More than 2,000 people have been arrested on college and university campuses since April 18, as a wave of pro-Palestinian protests ripples across the US. Follow for live updates. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Former UK PM Boris Johnson turned away from polling station after forgetting ID
item.description: Former British Prime Minister Boris Johnson was turned away from a polling station after forgetting to bring ID to vote in the U.K.’s local elections

item.title: May 2, 2024 - US college protests
item.description: Police are cracking down on protests against Israel's bombardment of Gaza at campuses across the US.

item.title: College protests updates: NYU authorizing NYPD to clear camp
item.description: Protests have broken out at colleges and universities across the country in connection with the war in Gaza.

item.title: Stormy Daniels' former lawyer testifies in Trump's hush money trial
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's hush money trial continues in New York.

item.title: Houston area faces 'life-threatening' flood conditions as severe weather hits Texas
item.description: Gov. Greg Abbott has issued a disaster declaration for dozens of counties in Texas on Thursday as severe weather and flooding threaten the state.

item.title: Biden to give Presidential Medal of Freedom to Pelosi, Gore, Bloomberg, Yeoh and more
item.description: President Joe Biden will honor 19 people with the Presidential Medal of Freedom on Friday, the nation’s highest civilian honor.

item.title: Pro-Palestinian protesters set up encampments at universities in Australia
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protesters are camped on university campuses across Australia, with some scuffling with pro-Israel protesters in Sydney, mirroring similar events in the United States
